<h2>Swollen gums and White patches on tongue</h2>
<p>WebMD Symptom Checker helps you find the most common medical conditions indicated by the symptoms swollen gums and white patches on tongue including Teething, Thrush (infants and children), and Toothbrush irritation.</p>
<p>There  are 5 conditions  associated with swollen gums and white patches on tongue. The links below will provide you with more detailed information on these medical conditions from the WebMD Symptom Checker and help provide a better understanding of causes and treatment of these related conditions.</p>
